Thiazide-like diuretics such as hydrochlorothiazide can cause hyperuricemia, due to increased uric acid reabsorption in the proximal tubule of the kidney. They do not typically cause hypocalcemia or hypoglycemia, and in fact, can sometimes cause hyperglycemia. Hypernatremia is more commonly associated with loop diuretics than thiazide-like diuretics.
